<!-- How to Use Google Fonts in an HTML Document
Choose a Font from Google Fonts

Visit Google Fonts and select the font(s) you want to use.
Click "Select this style" and copy the provided <link> tag or the @import code.
Integrate the Font in HTML

Add the <link> tag to the <head> section of your HTML document.
Use the font-family CSS property to apply the font to specific elements. -->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Google Fonts Example</title>

    <!-- Google Fonts Integration -->
    <link
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;700&family=Playfair+Display:wght@700&display=swap"
        rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        h1 {
            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
            font-size: 40px;
            font-weight: 700;
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>Using Google Fonts</h1>
    <p>
        This is a paragraph styled with the <code>Roboto</code> font. The heading above uses the
        <code>Playfair Display</code> font. Google Fonts makes it easy to incorporate beautiful typography
        into your website.
    </p>

</body>

</html>

<!-- Summary
Google Fonts allow you to integrate custom fonts from Googleâ€™s library, making typography more visually appealing.
Favicons improve website recognition by providing a small icon in the browser tab.
Both features can be easily integrated by adding appropriate <link> tags to the <head> section of the HTML document. This ensures a consistent and professional look for your web pages. -->